{"entryType":"UniProtKB reviewed (Swiss-Prot)","primaryAccession":"Q1HVG1","uniProtkbId":"BZLF1_EBVA8","entryAudit":{"firstPublicDate":"2011-05-03","lastAnnotationUpdateDate":"2023-11-08","lastSequenceUpdateDate":"2006-06-13","entryVersion":69,"sequenceVersion":1},"annotationScore":3.0,"organism":{"scientificName":"Epstein-Barr virus (strain AG876)","commonName":"HHV-4","synonyms":["Human herpesvirus 4"],"taxonId":82830,"lineage":["Viruses","Duplodnaviria","Heunggongvirae","Peploviricota","Herviviricetes","Herpesvirales","Herpesviridae","Gammaherpesvirinae","Lymphocryptovirus","Lymphocryptovirus humangamma4","Epstein-Barr virus (strain GD1)"]},"organismHosts":[{"scientificName":"Homo sapiens","commonName":"Human","taxonId":9606}],"proteinExistence":"3: Inferred from homology","proteinDescription":{"recommendedName":{"fullName":{"value":"Lytic switch protein BZLF1"},"shortNames":[{"value":"EB1"}]},"alternativeNames":[{"fullName":{"value":"Protein Z"}},{"fullName":{"value":"Trans-activator protein BZLF1"}},{"fullName":{"value":"Zebra"}},{"fullName":{"value":"Zta"}},{"fullName":{"value":"bZIP transcription factor ZEBRA"}}]},"genes":[{"orfNames":[{"value":"BZLF1"}]}],"comments":[{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250","source":"UniProtKB","id":"P03206"}],"value":"Transcription factor that acts as a molecular switch to induce the transition from the latent to the lytic or productive phase of the virus cycle. Mediates the switch from the latent to the lytic cycle of infection in cells containing a highly methylated viral genome. Probably binds to silenced chromatin and recruits host chromatin-remodeling enzymes. Regulates this switch by binding to 2 types of ZEBRA response elements (ZREs): the CpG-free AP-1 like elements (latency) and the methylated CpG-containing elements (lytic replication). Activates preferentially the methylated forms of the viral lytic R (BRLF1) and Na (BRRF1) gene promoters, the latters being the first genes activated during Z-mediated reactivation in latently infected cells. BZLF1 and BRLF1 act together to trigger lytic replication. Also binds the lytic origin of replication, oriLyt. Induces G1 cell cycle arrest by stabilizing the host CCAAT/enhancer binding protein CEBPA. This function is important because the lytic cycle preferentially takes place in host cells arrested in G1"}],"commentType":"FUNCTION"},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250","source":"UniProtKB","id":"P03206"}],"value":"Homodimer. Interacts (via b-ZIP domain) with the DNA polymerase processivity factor BMRF1 (via N-terminus); this interaction may inhibit BZLF1-induced transcription of the BMRF1 promoter. Interacts with human UBN1, CRTC2 and RACK1. Interacts (via N-terminus) with human PAX5 (via N-terminus); this interaction inhibits BZLF1-mediated lytic viral reactivation. Interacts (via leucine-zipper domain) with host CEBPA; this interaction induces G1 host cell cycle arrest. Interacts (via C-terminus) with host TP53BP1 (via C-terminus); this interaction is involved in the activation of the viral lytic cycle. Interacts with host chromatin-remodeling ATPase INO80; this interaction participates to the activation of early lytic viral genes by BZLF1. Interacts with host regulator of chromatin SMARCA5/hSNF2H; this interaction participates to the activation of early lytic viral genes by BZLF1. Interacts with host PLSCR1/Phospholipid scramblase 1; this interaction negatively regulates the transcriptional regulatory activity of BZLF1 by preventing the formation of the BZLF1-CBP complex"}],"commentType":"SUBUNIT"},{"commentType":"SUBCELLULAR LOCATION","subcellularLocations":[{"location":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250","source":"UniProtKB","id":"P03206"}],"value":"Host nucleus","id":"SL-0414"}}]},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000305"}],"value":"Expressed in the immediate-early phase of the viral replicative cycle (Probable). It is expressed again during the switch between latency and lytic replication (Probable)"}],"commentType":"INDUCTION"},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250","source":"UniProtKB","id":"P03206"}],"value":"Recognizes the CpG methylation marks through a specific serine and a methylcytosine-arginine-guanine triad. The leucine zipper region contributes to homodimerization. The basic motif is involved in specific DNA-binding"}],"commentType":"DOMAIN"},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000305"}],"value":"Belongs to the bZIP family"}],"commentType":"SIMILARITY"}],"features":[{"type":"Chain","location":{"start":{"value":1,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":245,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"Lytic switch protein BZLF1","featureId":"PRO_0000408267"},{"type":"Domain","location":{"start":{"value":178,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":228,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"bZIP"},{"type":"Region","location":{"start":{"value":1,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":167,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"Transactivation","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250","source":"UniProtKB","id":"P03206"}]},{"type":"Region","location":{"start":{"value":140,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":167,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"Disordered","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000256","source":"SAM","id":"MobiDB-lite"}]},{"type":"Region","location":{"start":{"value":178,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":195,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"Basic motif","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250"}]},{"type":"Region","location":{"start":{"value":196,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":228,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"Leucine-zipper","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250"}]},{"type":"Region","location":{"start":{"value":229,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":245,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"Accessory activation domain","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250","source":"UniProtKB","id":"P03206"}]},{"type":"Motif","location":{"start":{"value":157,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":194,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"